# Keep the Docker build context tiny: ignore everything not needed to build
# the C++ binary and run the web server.
#
# What the image actually needs (see Dockerfile):
#   cpp/ (source, minus build/) ; agricola/ ; play.py ; play_web.py ;
#   static/ ; templates/ ; nn_models/cpp_export_best's resolved target dir.

# Version control / tooling
.git
.gitignore
.pytest_cache
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
DEPLOY.md
fly.toml

# Python caches
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Tests: exclude the suite, but KEEP test_utils.py — agricola/agents/base.py
# (and other agent modules) import `filter_implemented` from it at module load
# (a known code smell). `tests/*` (not `tests/`) lets the two files be
# re-included below so the import resolves in the image.
tests/*
!tests/__init__.py
!tests/test_utils.py
data/
nn_runs/
eval_out/
tuned_configs/
archive/
design_docs/
Rulebooks/
scripts/

# Local C++ build (the Mach-O arm64 artifact; rebuilt for Linux in-image)
cpp/build/

# Docs (none are load-bearing at runtime)
*.md

# Trained-model checkpoints are large and not needed — EXCEPT the C++ export
# the symlink resolves to, which the Dockerfile copies explicitly. Ignore all
# of nn_models/, then un-ignore the one resolved weights dir.
nn_models/
!nn_models/cpp_export_joint_taper128_thin_sp30k_lr3e4_ep17/
